<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Bootstrap Directory Structure Explanation</title>
  
  <!-- Link to Bootstrap CSS -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/bootstrap.min.css">
</head>
<body>

  <div class="container mt-5">
    <h1 class="text-primary text-center">Bootstrap Directory Structure</h1>
    
    <div class="mt-4">
      <h3>1. <code>css/</code> Folder</h3>
      <p>This folder contains the <strong>compiled CSS files</strong> such as <code>bootstrap.min.css</code>, which provides styling for HTML elements using Bootstrap's predefined classes.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4">
      <h3>2. <code>js/</code> Folder</h3>
      <p>This folder contains the <strong>compiled JavaScript files</strong> like <code>bootstrap.bundle.min.js</code>. These files include Bootstrap's JavaScript components such as modals, tooltips, and carousels, often bundled with Popper.js.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4">
      <h3>3. <code>icons/</code> Folder (Optional)</h3>
      <p>If downloaded, this folder contains the <strong>Bootstrap Icons</strong> library. You can use SVG or font-based icons in your project by linking the icons CSS file and referencing icon classes in your HTML.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Link to Bootstrap JS -->
  <script src="js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
